article.description: — James Bishop had 18 points as George Washington beat Wright State 74-63 on Monday.
article.headline: Bishop leads George Washington past Wright State 74-63
article.linkText: Bishop leads George Washington past Wright State 74-63
article.story: NAPLES, Fla. -- — James Bishop had 18 points as George Washington beat Wright State 74-63 on Monday. Joe Bamisile had 15 points and nine rebounds for George Washington (2-4), which ended its four-game losing streak. Ricky Lindo Jr. added 12 points and six assists, and Brendan Adams had 10 points. Tanner Holden had 24 points and eight rebounds for the Raiders (1-3). Tim Finke added 12 points and nine rebounds, and Grant Basile had 11 points, 13 rebounds and three blocks. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
